<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     PAGE 3 — TERMS & CONDITIONS (CLAUSES 1–12)
     ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

<div class="top-bar"></div>
<div class="page-header">
  <div class="ph-left">{{company.name}} &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp; Letter of Appointment</div>
  <div class="ph-right">{{employee.full_name}} &nbsp;|&nbsp; {{today}}</div>
</div>

<div class="body">

  <div class="tc-heading">Terms &amp; Conditions of Employment</div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">1</span> Commencement &amp; Nature of Employment</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">Your employment with <strong>{{company.name}}</strong> shall commence on
    <strong>{{#if employee.joining_date}}{{formatDate employee.joining_date "DD-MMM-YYYY"}}{{else}}{{formatDate employee.date_of_joining "DD-MMM-YYYY"}}{{/if}}</strong>
    or such other date mutually agreed in writing. Your appointment is on a regular, full-time basis
    and you are expected to devote your full working time, attention, and abilities to the company
    and its business interests.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">2</span> Probation Period</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">You will be on a probationary period of <strong>six (6) calendar months</strong>
    from your date of joining. Upon satisfactory completion and subject to a formal performance review,
    your employment will be confirmed. The company reserves the right to extend the probationary period
    by a further period not exceeding <strong>three (3) months</strong> at its sole discretion,
    by issuing written notice before the expiry of the original probationary period.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">3</span> Notice Period</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>During Probation:</strong> Either party may terminate this employment by giving <strong>One (1) month's written notice</strong> or payment of one month's gross salary in lieu of notice.</li>
        <li><strong>Post Confirmation:</strong> Either party may terminate this employment by giving <strong>One (1) month's written notice</strong> or payment of one month's gross salary in lieu of notice.</li>
        <li>The company reserves the right to terminate your employment immediately, without notice or payment in lieu, in cases of gross misconduct, fraud, wilful negligence, breach of confidentiality, or any other cause that justifies summary dismissal.</li>
        <li>Notice must be submitted in writing and addressed to the HR Department. Notice periods cannot be adjusted against accumulated leave, except with prior written approval of the management.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">4</span> Working Hours &amp; Days</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">Standard working hours are <strong>9 hours per day (including 1 hour lunch break)</strong>,
    five to six days a week, as per the applicable shift roster. You may be required to work beyond regular
    hours, on weekends, or on public holidays based on business requirements, without any additional
    overtime compensation unless specifically agreed in writing. Flexible work arrangements, if any,
    shall be at the sole discretion of the company.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">5</span> Remuneration &amp; Tax Obligations</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">Your remuneration will be paid monthly, directly into your designated
    bank account, on or before the last working day of each calendar month. The salary is subject to
    applicable TDS (Tax Deducted at Source) as per the Income Tax Act, 1961. You are solely responsible
    for filing your income tax returns and maintaining correct investment declarations. Any tax liability
    arising due to incorrect or delayed declarations shall be borne by you.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">6</span> Confidentiality &amp; Non-Disclosure</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">During and after your employment, you shall maintain strict confidentiality
    of all proprietary and sensitive information, including but not limited to:
      <ul>
        <li>Business strategies, plans, and financial data</li>
        <li>Client and vendor lists, contact information, and agreements</li>
        <li>Technical specifications, source code, algorithms, and product roadmaps</li>
        <li>Employee compensation and personal data</li>
        <li>Any information marked or reasonably understood to be confidential</li>
      </ul>
    Breach of this clause shall entitle the company to seek injunctive relief, damages, and other
    remedies available under applicable law, including the Information Technology Act, 2000.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">7</span> Intellectual Property Rights</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">All inventions, discoveries, developments, improvements, designs, software,
    reports, documents, creative works, and any other output conceived, developed, or produced by you
    in the course of your employment — whether on company premises or otherwise — shall be the exclusive
    property of <strong>{{company.name}}</strong>. You hereby irrevocably assign all intellectual property
    rights in such works to the company and agree to execute any further instruments necessary to perfect
    such assignment.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">8</span> Non-Solicitation</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">During the term of your employment and for a period of <strong>twelve (12)
    months following termination</strong> of your employment for any reason, you shall not, directly or
    indirectly: (a) solicit, induce, or encourage any employee, contractor, or consultant of the company
    to leave their employment or engagement; or (b) solicit, approach, or do business with any client,
    customer, or prospect of the company with whom you had contact or exposure during your employment.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">9</span> Conflict of Interest &amp; Dual Employment</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">You are required to devote your entire working time and efforts exclusively
    to <strong>{{company.name}}</strong>. You shall not, during the period of employment:
      <ul>
        <li>Take up any other employment, consultancy, directorship, or business engagement — paid or unpaid — without prior written approval from management.</li>
        <li>Hold any financial or personal interest that conflicts with the interests of the company.</li>
        <li>Accept gifts, commissions, or consideration from clients, vendors, or competitors beyond nominal value.</li>
      </ul>
    Violation of this clause shall constitute grounds for immediate termination.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">10</span> Background Verification</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">This offer is conditional upon satisfactory completion of a pre-employment
    background verification, which may include verification of educational qualifications, previous
    employment records, character references, criminal record checks, and document authenticity.
    If any information provided by you is found to be false, misleading, or incomplete at any point —
    even after joining — the company reserves the right to terminate your employment without notice
    or any compensation.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">11</span> Document Submission</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">You are required to submit the following original documents along with
    self-attested photocopies on or before your date of joining:
      <ul>
        <li>All educational qualification certificates (10th, 12th, Degree, PG, certifications)</li>
        <li>Previous employment experience letters and relieving letters</li>
        <li>Last three months' salary slips and appointment letter from last employer</li>
        <li>Government-issued photo ID proof (Aadhaar / Passport / Voter ID / Driving Licence)</li>
        <li>PAN card copy, passport-size photographs (4 nos.), and cancelled cheque</li>
        <li>Any other documents as requested by HR at the time of onboarding</li>
      </ul>
    Failure to produce required documents may result in withdrawal of this offer or termination.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tc-block">
    <div class="tc-clause-title"><span class="clause-num">12</span> Code of Conduct &amp; Discipline</div>
    <div class="tc-clause-body">You are expected to conduct yourself professionally and ethically at all
    times. You shall adhere to the company's Employee Handbook, Code of Conduct, HR Policies, IT Security
    Policy, and any other policies or guidelines issued from time to time. Acts of misconduct, insubordination,
    dishonesty, harassment (including sexual harassment), violence, or wilful damage to company property
    shall be grounds for disciplinary action, including summary termination.</div>
  </div>

</div>

